{"word":"ἐγκυκλόω","slug":"ἐγκυκλόω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐγκυκλόω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ώσω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to move round in a circle</i>, <el>τι</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to encircle</i>, <el>φωνή μέ τις ἐγκεκύκλωται</el> a voice <i>has echoed around me</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> <i>to roam about</i> a place, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}